description:
&lt;p&gt;Full-Time Position&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for an experienced chef to join our excellent kitchen team. The successful candidate will contribute to the provision of approximately 1000 patient meals per day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All our staff are100% committed to delivering the best possible service to our patients and customers, maintaining a high quality service, and assisting us to sustain our 5 Star Food Hygiene Rating&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a valued team member you will need to be an innovative and motivated person who will seek to improve an already successful unit. Focusing on customer satisfaction at all times you will need to have excellent people skills and keen to work as part of a successful team, you will be flexible, reliable, and keen to progress. The successful candidate will have previous experience of working in a busy kitchen producing quality fresh food and be keen to be involved in development work and service improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work on a rostered shift pattern that includes working every other weekend. Shifts are 8 hours per day between the hours of 7am – 6pm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates should be qualified to a minimum standard of City &amp; Guilds 706 1/ 2 or equivalent, a level 2 in Nutrition, and a minimum of Foundation Level 2 in Food Hygiene.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Paul Page&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Catering Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address paul.page1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01536492015&lt;/p&gt;
